Two goals in the last six minutes gave Japan an unbeaten 2-1 victory over Syria in the Asian Cup on Friday.
In the 88th minute of the Group C match, Takagi headed home the winner after goalkeeper Salem Bitar broke up an error-free display by letting the ball slip under his body.
It was Syria's second defensive error in four minutes.
In the 84th minute, defender Hassan Abass rose to intercept a long ball into the box, but could only deflect it into the top corner of Bitar's goal.

Japan then laid siege to the Syrian penalty area and had a goal disallowed in the 16th minute because the ball was headed behind.
A minute later, Bitars made a good double attack, first deflecting a Kazuyoshi Miura header and then blocking Takagi's shot.
